<p>Acushnet Company, an operating company of Fortune Brands,
is the industry leader in golf equipment, comprising the Titleist, FootJoy,
Pinnacle, Cobra, and Scotty Cameron brands, with sales exceeding $1B.

<p>OASIS, Acushnet’s mobile Sales Automation tool, is the
primary order entry mechanism for Acushnet’s staff of mobile Sales Reps.
OASIS was in its seventh year of production, running on an aging
PowerBuilder technology platform, with very high maintenance costs and
inadequate flexibility to meet the demands of a growing, changing business.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>Acushnet engaged Nevo to:
<ul>
<li>Re-architect OASIS to create a foundation for integrated order processing across the enterprise
</li><li>Rewrite OASIS on a more contemporary technology platform to ensure maintainability and extensibility
</li><li>Redesign the information architecture and user interface to greatly simplify the order process, increase usability and decrease training costs
</li><li>Increase the flexibility of the application to facilitate the addition of new companies, product lines, and product definitions
</li>
</ul>

<font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>Nevo selected Microsoft’s .NET platform for the new OASIS.
We designed a metadata-driven architecture to take advantage of Acushnet’s
extensive product definition resources and to enable real-time flexible
product and brand definition. We reverse engineered the PowerBuilder
code to capture undocumented business rules, redesigned and greatly
simplified the user interface, and added significant functionality
while delivering the new OASIS on budget and in time for Acushnet’s
annual sales meetings.  The new system was greeted with rave reviews,
it was rapidly adopted, training costs for new Acushnet Sales Reps
plummeted and order efficiency increased significantly.
<p>Following the first release of the new OASIS in 2003,
Nevo delivered a Canadian release later in the year, and a multi-currency
European release in 2004.

